<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-440-709  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 440 709.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 16 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Speech recognition to be added to TravelNet phone card.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Telesphere (contracts)Voice Control Systems Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Voice RecognitionContractsTravelNet (Telephone service)Telecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SPEECH RECOGNITION TO BE ADDED TO TRAVELNET PHONE CARD OAKBROOK TERRACE,ILLINOIS, U.S.A., 1990 AUG 16 (NB) -- Telesphere signed an agreement withVoice Control Systems of Dallas to integrate voice recognition and speakerverification technology into Telesphere's TravelNet calling card.andP;  The newfeature will allow users to speak, instead of dial, authorization codes anddestination telephone numbers.andM;Telesphere said fraud resulting from lost or stolen credit cards will beminimized, since a thief would have to be able to imitate accurately theowner's voice when trying to make an unauthorized call.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900810/Press Contact: Scott Moster, Telesphere,708-954-7700)</TEXT></DOC>